<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="149" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[822,1467,1817,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">
This species was initially recorded as 
<taxonomicName authority="Reissinger, 1990" authorityName="Reissinger" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Leptidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reali">
<emphasis box="[1212,1349,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">Leptidea reali</emphasis>
Reissinger, 1990
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[822,1467,1817,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">
For the moment, the occurrence in 
<collectingCountry box="[1168,1211,1923,1947]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">Italy</collectingCountry>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1946" box="[1242,1355,1923,1947]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Leptidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juvernica">
<emphasis box="[1242,1355,1923,1947]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">L. juvernica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a small number of specimens from the E Alps (V. Dincă, in litt.). The “non 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[919,1005,1976,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Leptidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinapis">
<emphasis box="[919,1005,1976,1999]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">L. sinapis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations” of C 
<collectingCountry box="[1186,1229,1976,2000]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">Italy</collectingCountry>
have been demonstrated to represent 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reissinger" authorityYear="1990" box="[943,1011,2002,2026]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Leptidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reali">
<emphasis box="[943,1011,2002,2026]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">L. reali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DINCA V. &amp; LUKHTANOV V. A. &amp; TALAVERA G. &amp; VILA R." box="[1027,1198,2002,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref19538" refString="DINCA V., LUKHTANOV V. A., TALAVERA G. &amp; VILA R. 2011. - Unexpected layers of cryptic diversity in wood white Leptidea butterflies. Nature Communications 2 (324): 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2011">
Dincă 
<emphasis box="[1093,1140,2002,2026]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="DINCA V. &amp; WIKLUND C. &amp; KODANDARAMAIAH U. &amp; NOREN K. &amp; PORTO L. &amp; WAHLBERG N. &amp; VILA R. &amp; FRIBERG M." box="[1208,1263,2002,2026]" pageId="9" pageNumber="148" refId="ref19580" refString="DINCA V., WIKLUND C., V. A., KODANDARAMAIAH U., NOREN K., DAP- PORTO L., WAHLBERG N., VILA R. &amp; FRIBERG M. 2013. - Reproductive isolation and patterns of genetic differentiation in a cryptic butterfly species complex. Journal of Evolutionary Biology http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / jeb. 12211" type="book" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
). In N 
<collectingCountry box="[1334,1378,2002,2026]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="148">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 25 “non
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[452,1109,1194,1212]" box="[452,1109,1194,1212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
FIG 2. — 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[527,868,1194,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Parnassius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mnemosyne">
<emphasis box="[527,723,1194,1212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Parnassius mnemosyne</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS C." box="[733,864,1194,1212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 824" refId="ref21540" refString="LINNAEUS C. 1758. - Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classses, ordines, genera, species. Editio decima reformata, Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae. vol. 1: 1 - 824." type="journal article" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Photograph: Davide Piccoli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="149" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="10.[121,764,1261,1365]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[121,210,1262,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Leptidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinapis">
<emphasis box="[121,210,1262,1285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">L. sinapis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations” have been recorded, but no molecular data are currently available for the Valdieri area. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1946" box="[632,744,1288,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Leptidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juvernica">
<emphasis box="[632,744,1288,1311]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">L. juvernica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur at least in NE 
<collectingCountry box="[416,460,1314,1338]" name="Italy" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">Italy</collectingCountry>
, at the Val di Tovo lakes (
<bibRefCitation author="DINCA V. &amp; LUKHTANOV V. A. &amp; TALAVERA G. &amp; VILA R." pageId="10" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref19538" refString="DINCA V., LUKHTANOV V. A., TALAVERA G. &amp; VILA R. 2011. - Unexpected layers of cryptic diversity in wood white Leptidea butterflies. Nature Communications 2 (324): 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2011">
Dincă 
<emphasis box="[121,168,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="149">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="DINCA V. &amp; WIKLUND C. &amp; KODANDARAMAIAH U. &amp; NOREN K. &amp; PORTO L. &amp; WAHLBERG N. &amp; VILA R. &amp; FRIBERG M." box="[237,292,1341,1365]" pageId="10" pageNumber="149" refId="ref19580" refString="DINCA V., WIKLUND C., V. A., KODANDARAMAIAH U., NOREN K., DAP- PORTO L., WAHLBERG N., VILA R. &amp; FRIBERG M. 2013. - Reproductive isolation and patterns of genetic differentiation in a cryptic butterfly species complex. Journal of Evolutionary Biology http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / jeb. 12211" type="book" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
